Pharmacology of pregnancy and lactation

Factor affecting placental drug transfer

  • Highly lipid-soluble = easily to fetus
  • placental blood flow
  • Highly ionized drug = hardly to fetus
  • Large molecular size = hardly to fetus
  • Heparin placenta pregnancy hypercoagulable state
  • pH (basis) = trap in fetus
  • Maternal blood pH = 7.4
  • Fetal blood pH = 7.3
  • Basis drug ion trapping fetus
  • protein binding = hardly to fetus
  • poorly lipid-soluble & ionized

Placental transporter

  • IgG placenta 2ndtrimester
  • Transporter efflux fetus
  • P-glycoprotein transporter = viral protease inhibitor (anti-HIV)
  • BCRP & MRP3 transporter = hypoglycemic drug

Placental & fetal drug metabolism

  • Placenta semipermeable barrier & site of metabolism
  • Ethanol toxic metabolite
  • Pentobarbital oxidized pentobarbital
  • Prednisolone inactive prednisone = pregnancy
